  "support_faq": "Frequently Asked Questions",
  "support_faq_1_q": "How are claims triggered?",
  "support_faq_1_a": "Our app monitors official data feeds 24/7. When a disruption (heavy rain, extreme heat, air pollution, or platform downtime) is confirmed in your zone, a claim is created automatically. You don't need to do anything—no documents, no waiting.",
  "support_faq_2_q": "When will I receive my payout?",
  "support_faq_2_a": "Fast & automatic: 70% is credited to your UPI within minutes after the claim is approved. The remaining 30% follows within 48 hours. Our system cross-checks your GPS location with platform login data to ensure you were actively working.",
  "support_faq_3_q": "What if I miss a disruption alert?",
  "support_faq_3_a": "You can file a manual claim directly from the app. Go to Claims → Report Disruption, describe the issue, and submit live evidence from your phone's camera. Our AI verifies it within 24 hours.",
  "support_faq_4_q": "Can I upgrade or downgrade my coverage?",
  "support_faq_4_a": "Yes, anytime. Go to Policy → Upgrade Plan to switch between Standard Shield (₹49/week) and Full Shield (₹79/week). Changes take effect on the next Monday.",
  "support_faq_5_q": "How are weekly premiums calculated?",
  "support_faq_5_a": "Your premium is based on: (1) historical disruption probability in your zone, (2) your platform's uptime rate, and (3) your personal claim history. Cleaner records → lower premiums. That's why Hustlr rewards trust.",
  "support_faq_6_q": "What if no disruptions happen in my zone?",
  "support_faq_6_a": "Great! You're protected either way. If your zone stays clear for 4 consecutive weeks, you unlock a 10% cashback on your premiums (Full Shield only). The app tracks this automatically.",
  "support_faq_7_q": "How do I withdraw my payout balance?",
  "support_faq_7_a": "Open Wallet → tap Withdraw. Enter your UPI ID (same as your registered Razorpay). Transfers are instant and free—no hidden charges. Money lands in your bank within 2 hours.",
  "support_raise_ticket": "Raise a Ticket",
  "support_ticket_placeholder": "Describe your issue...",
  "support_submit": "Submit Ticket",

